<TITLE> Second Pilkhana mutiny trial begins </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 31 (bdnews24.com)  Trial of mutiny suspects belonging to 24 Rifles Battalion began at Pilkhana in Dhaka on Wednesday, the second of the mutiny trials in the capital. The special court at the Darbar Hall in Pilkhana, with BDR director general Maj Gen Moinul Islam in the chair, began proceedings at around 10am. Charges were read out against 668 mutineers and 302 were shown arrested in the day's proceedings. Trial of some 310 mutineers of 36 Rifles Battalion also began last month at the same court. Over 70 people, 57 of them army officers deputed to the border force, were killed during the mutiny on Feb 25-26 2009. The government formed six special courts last year, including two in Dhaka, to try approximately 3,500 border guards belonging to a number of different units have been accused in 40 separate cases in connection with the mutiny and associated rebellions in other district
